meta {
  name: GET /health — liveness
  type: http
  seq: 1
}

get {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/health
  body: none
  auth: none
}

assert {
  res.status: eq 200
  res.body.status: eq ok
  res.headers['x-correlation-id']: isDefined
}

docs {
  # Liveness

  **What it proves:** the sidecar process is up and Fastify is serving
  requests. No dependency is touched — this is the cheap "is it alive"
  probe (Railway healthcheck target). Dependency health is `/ready`.

  **Expected response** — `200`:

  ```json
  { "status": "ok" }
  ```

  **Also asserted:** the `x-correlation-id` response header. Every request
  to the sidecar gets a correlation ID (an incoming `x-correlation-id`
  header is honored, otherwise one is generated) that appears on every log
  line, tool call, and LLM interaction — a full trace reconstructs from
  logs alone. The header proves that plumbing is active.
}
